  <prompt>
    Create the new shared package `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/` per Pattern D, mirroring `@spaarke/events-components` (Calendar) and `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` precedent. Include `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, build config, and an empty `src/` skeleton with subpath structure (`components/`, `widgets/`, `hooks/`, `services/`, `types/`). The package builds (empty index.ts is fine) and is consumable from the monorepo. No business code moves in this task — that's tasks 011–013.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in monorepo TypeScript package layout, `@spaarke/events-components` precedent, and Pattern D dual-use widget shape.</role>

  <goal>New package skeleton exists; `npm run build` succeeds in the new package; the empty subpath exports are reachable from a consumer test import.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-03 and FR-10: a new dedicated package per Calendar/SmartTodo precedent. NOT extending `@spaarke/ui-components`. This task lays the foundation; all subsequent P2 tasks populate it.
