  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `Spaarke.Events.Components/package.json` and `tsconfig.json` to identify the canonical layout.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/` with the same shape (package.json, tsconfig.json, src/index.ts, src/components/index.ts, src/widgets/index.ts, src/hooks/index.ts, src/services/index.ts, src/types/index.ts).</step>
    <step order="3">Set package name to `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` (per spec assumption; flag if owner prefers shorter name).</step>
    <step order="4">Set up subpath exports in `package.json` exports map matching Calendar precedent.</step>
    <step order="5">Register the new package in the monorepo workspace config (`package.json` workspaces / `pnpm-workspace.yaml` / equivalent — match how Calendar is registered).</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm install` and `npm run build` in the new package; verify both succeed.</step>
    <step order="7">From any consumer (e.g., add a temporary import test), verify `import { } from '@spaarke/daily-briefing-components/components'` resolves.</step>
